“Encapsulation is the process of wrapping data and methods into a single unit and restricting direct access 
 to the data using access modifiers.

 Key idea : Data hiding

 👉 Encapsulation = Data + Methods bundled together + Controlled access

Instead of letting anyone directly change your data, you protect it and allow access only through defined methods.

👉 Think: “I decide how my data is used”


⚡ Easy Analogy (Yaad rakhne ke liye)

👉 Capsule (medicine) 💊

Bahar cover hota hai (protection)
Andar medicine hoti hai (data)

👉 Tum direct medicine ko touch nahi karte
👉 Tum sirf capsule lete ho

✔ Same → data hidden + controlled access


# Inheritance :

“Inheritance is a mechanism in which one class acquires properties and behavior of another class, allowing code reuse and hierarchy creation.”